# Lien Project Rules

`CLAUDE.md` at the repo root is the single source of truth for project
structure, mandatory MCP tool usage, and commit gates — read it. This file is
deliberately thin: a duplicated package tree or gate list drifts out of sync
the moment either side changes (as this file previously did for months).

**Load-bearing facts, kept minimal on purpose:**
- Packages: `parser` ← `core` ← `cli` (published as `@liendev/parser` /
  `@liendev/core` / `@liendev/lien`); `review`/`action`/`site` are private and
  unpublished. `review` depends on `parser` only, not `core`.
- Storage is SQLite + FTS5 lexical (BM25) search only — no embeddings, no
  vector DB.
- Before every commit, no exceptions: `npm run format:check`, `npm run lint`,
  `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`, `npm test`, `lien delta`.
- Commits follow Conventional Commits (`feat(scope): ...`, `fix(scope): ...`);
  never `git commit --amend`.
